00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,000
And I'm saying you're a liar--

364
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:44,000
And after you found out she was a morphine addict, why

365
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,000
didn't you send her on a cure then, at the start when she

366
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,000
still had a chance?

367
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,000
No, no that would've meant spending some money.

368
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,000
But you told her all she had to do was

369
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,000
use a little willpower.

370
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,000
Haven't I've spent thousands and thousands on cures?

371
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:54,000
What good have they done?

372
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,000
As of late, she's always started again.

373
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,000
Because you've never given her anything that would help her

374
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,000
want to stay off it.

375
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:02,000
No home except for this summer dump in a place that she hates

376
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,000
and you refused even to spend money to make this look decent

377
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,000
while you keep buying more property, playing sucker for

378
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:10,000
every conman with a gold mine or a silver mine or any kind

379
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,000
of get-rich-quick swindle.

380
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:14,000
You've dragged her around on the road, season after season,

381
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,000
on one night stands with no one she could talk to, waiting

382
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,000
night after night in dirty hotel rooms for you to come

383
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,000
back with a bun on after the bars closed.

384
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:25,000
Christ. Is it any wonder she didn't want to be cured?

385
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,000
Jesus, Papa, when I think of it, I hate your guts.

386
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:31,000
Edmund, how dare you talk to your father like that-- you

387
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,000
insolent young cub-- after all I've done for you?

388
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,000
Yeah, we'll come to that, what you're doing for me.

389
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:38,000
Will you stop repeating your mother's crazy accusations,

390
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:41,000
which she never makes unless it's the poison talking?

391
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,000
I never dragged her on the road against her will.

392
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Naturally I wanted her with me because I loved her and she

393
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,000
came with me because she loved me.

394
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,000
And that's the truth no matter what she says

395
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,000
when she's not herself.

396
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,000
And she needn't have been lonely.

397
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,000
She always had the members of my company to talk to if

398
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,000
she'd wanted to.

399
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:59,000
She had the children too and I insisted--

400
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,000
in spite of the expense-- on having a nurse to

401
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,000
travel with her too.

