00:18:48,000 --> 00:19:02,000


420
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,000
I'm like Mama.

421
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:11,000
I can't help liking you in spite of everything.

422
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:24,000


423
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,000
I might say the same thing about you.

424
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:30,000
You're no great shakes as a son.

425
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:42,000
It's a case of, "A poor thing but mine own." What happened

426
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,000
to our game?

427
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:46,000
Whose play is it?

428
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,000
Yours, I guess.

429
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:51,000


430
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,000
You mustn't be too down-hearted, lad, by the bad

431
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,000
news you had today.

432
00:19:56,000 --> 00:20:01,000
Both the doctors said that if you obey orders in this place

433
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:05,000
you're going to, you'll be cured in six months to a year

434
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,000
at most.

435
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:12,000
Don't kid me.

436
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,000
You don't believe that.

437
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Well of course I believe it.

438
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,000
Why shouldn't I when both Hardy and the specialist--

439
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,000
You think I'm going to die.

440
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:19,000
That's a lie.

441
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:19,000
You're crazy.

442
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:22,000
So why waste money?

443
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,000
That's why you're sending me to the state farm.

444
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:29,000


445
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:32,000
What state farm?

446
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,000
It's the Hilltown Sanatorium.

447
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,000
That's all I know.

448
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,000
Both the doctors said it was the best place for you.

449
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,000
For the money.

450
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,000
That is for nothing or practically nothing.

451
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:45,000
Come on, don't lie, Papa.

452
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,000
You know damn well the Hilltown Sanatorium is a state

453
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
institution.

454
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,000
I mean, Jamie suspected you'd cry poorhouse to Hardy, he

455
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,000
wormed the truth out of him.

456
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,000
That drunken loafer, I'll kick him out into the gutter, he's

457
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,000
poisoned your mind against me ever since you were

458
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,000
old enough to listen.

459
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,000
You can't deny it's the truth about the state farm, can you?

460
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Well it's not true the way you look at it.

461
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,000
What if it is run by the state?

462
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,000
That's nothing against it.

463
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,000
The state has money to make a better place than any private

464
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,000
sanatorium.

465
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,000
And why shouldn't I take advantage of it?

466
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,000
It's my right and yours.

467
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,000
We're residents.

468
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,000
I'm a property owner.

469
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:14,000
I help to support it.

470
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,000
God knows, I'm taxed to death.

471
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,000
Yes, on property valued at a quarter of a million.

472
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:17,000
That's lies.

473
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,000
It's all mortgaged.

474
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,000
Hardy and the specialist know what you're worth.

475
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,000
I wonder what they thought when they heard you moaning

476
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,000
poorhouse and showing you wanted to

477
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,000
wish me on to charity.

478
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:24,000
That's a lie.

479
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,000
All I told them was I couldn't afford any millionaire's

480
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:26,000
sanatorium.

481
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:28,000
And that because I was land poor, and that's the truth.

482
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Yeah, then you went to the club and you met McGuire and

483
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,000
let him stick you with another bum piece of property.

484
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,000
Don't lie about it.

485
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,000
We met McGuire in the hotel bar after he left you.

486
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,000
Don't lie about it.

487
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:42,000


488
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,000
God, Papa.

489
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:53,000


490
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:57,000
Ever since I went to sea and was on my own and found out

491
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,000
what hard work for little pay was, and what it felt like to

492
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:03,000
be broke and starve and camp out on park benches--

493
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:06,000
because I had no place to sleep--

494
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:09,000
I've tried to be fair to you because I knew what you've

495
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:12,000
been up against as a kid.

496
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:14,000
I've tried to make allowances.

497
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:16,000
God knows you've got to make allowances in this damn family

498
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,000
or go nuts.

499
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:20,000
And I've tried to make allowances for myself when I

500
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,000
remember all the rotten stuff I've pulled.

501
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:27,000
And I've tried to feel like Mama, that you can't being

502
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,000
what you are where money is concerned.

503
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:33,000
But God almighty, this last stunt of yours is too much.

504
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:37,000
It makes me want to puke, and not because of the rotten way

505
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,000
you're treating me-- to hell with that I've treated you

506
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,000
rottenly in my own way more than once--

507
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:46,000
but to think, when it's a question of your own son

508
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,000
having consumption you can show yourself up in front of

509
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:52,000
the whole town as such a stinking, old tightwad.

510
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:54,000
Don't you know Hardy will talk?

511
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,000
The whole damn town will know.

512
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:56,000
Jesus, Papa.

513
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:58,000
Don't you have any pride or shame?

514
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:03,000


515
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:07,000
And don't think I'll let you get away with it.

516
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:10,000
I'm not going to damn state farm to save you a few lousy

517
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:16,000
bucks to buy more bum property with, you stinking, old miser.

518
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,000
Be quiet.

519
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,000
Don't say that to me.

520
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:19,000
You're drunk.

521
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:22,000
I won't mind you.

522
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,000
Stop coughing, lad.

523
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,000
You've got yourself worked up over nothing.

524
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,000
Who said you had to go to this Hilltown place.

525
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,000
You can go any place you like.

526
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,000
I don't care what it costs.

527
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,000
All I care is to have you get well.

528
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:32,000
Just don't call me a stinking old miser because I don't want

529
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,000
those doctors to think I'm some God damn millionaire they

530
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,000
can swindle.

531
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:44,000


532
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:45,000
You look weak, lad.

533
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:49,000


534
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,000
You'd better have a bracer.

535
00:23:50,000 --> 00:24:11,000


536
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:14,000
Whose play is it?

537
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:21,000


538
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,000
A stinking old miser.

539
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:27,000


540
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,000
Well, maybe you're right.

541
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:31,000


542
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,000
Maybe I can't help being--

